# Backend Environment Variables (for Koyeb deployment)
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@host/database?sslmode=require
SESSION_SECRET=your-super-secret-session-key-here
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-oauth-client-secret
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-backend-url.koyeb.app/api/auth/google/callback
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-url.vercel.app

# Frontend Environment Variables (for Vercel deployment)
VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.koyeb.app

# Instructions:
# 1. For Backend (Koyeb):
#    - Set all variables above in your Koyeb environment
#    - DATABASE_URL should point to your Neon PostgreSQL database
#    - SESSION_SECRET should be a random, secure string
#    - Google OAuth credentials from Google Cloud Console
#    - GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI should match your backend domain
#    - FRONTEND_URL should be your Vercel app URL for CORS
#
# 2. For Frontend (Vercel):
#    - Only set VITE_API_URL pointing to your deployed backend
#    - Example: VITE_API_URL=https://running-kimberli-suhailtechlnf-4b28b6a4.koyeb.app
#
# 3. Database Setup:
#    - Create a Neon PostgreSQL database
#    - Run: npm run db:push (from your local environment with DATABASE_URL set)
#    - This will create all necessary tables